<li id="cite_note-152"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-152">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFMohamed" class="citation web cs1">Mohamed, Hisham Yousif Hassan. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://khartoumspace.uofk.edu/bitstream/handle/123456789/6376/Genetic%20Patterns%20of%20Y-chromosome%20and%20Mitochondrial.pdf?sequence=1">"Genetic Patterns of Y-chromosome and Mitochondrial DNA Variation, with Implications to the Peopling of the Sudan"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. University of Khartoum<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">13 October</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Genetic+Patterns+of+Y-chromosome+and+Mitochondrial+DNA+Variation%2C+with+Implications+to+the+Peopling+of+the+Sudan&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Khartoum&amp;rft.aulast=Mohamed&amp;rft.aufirst=Hisham+Yousif+Hassan&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkhartoumspace.uofk.edu%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F6376%2FGenetic%2520Patterns%2520of%2520Y-chromosome%2520and%2520Mitochondrial.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACopts" class="Z3988"></span><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span style="white-space: nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot"><span title="&#160;Dead link tagged March 2020">permanent dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Dobon2015-cae-153"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Dobon2015-cae_153-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFBegoña_Dobon2015" class="citation journal cs1">Begoña Dobon;  et&#160;al. (28 May 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4446898">"The genetics of East African populations: a Nilo-Saharan component in the African genetic landscape"</a>. <i>Scientific Reports</i>. <b>5</b>: 8. <a href="/wiki/Bibcode_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Bibcode (identifier)">Bibcode</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2015NatSR...5E9996D">2015NatSR...5E9996D</a>. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1038%2Fsrep09996">10.1038/srep09996</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4446898">4446898</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26017457">26017457</a>. <q>The North African/Middle Eastern genetic component is identified especially in Copts. The Coptic population present in Sudan is an example of a recent migration from Egypt over the past two centuries. They are close to Egyptians in the PCA, but remain a differentiated cluster, showing their own component at k = 4 (Fig. 3). The Coptic component at k = 4 peaks highest among Copts and makes up most of their distribution while it is not predominant among Egyptians. K = 2 to K = 5 (Fig. 3) shows Egyptians distribution resemble Qatar more than Copts. Copts lack the influence found in Egyptians from Qatar, an Arabic population. It may suggest that Copts have a genetic composition that could resemble the ancestral Egyptian population, without the present strong Arab influence</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Scientific+Reports&amp;rft.atitle=The+genetics+of+East+African+populations%3A+a+Nilo-Saharan+component+in+the+African+genetic+landscape&amp;rft.volume=5&amp;rft.pages=8&amp;rft.date=2015-05-28&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4446898%23id-name%3DPMC&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F26017457&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1038%2Fsrep09996&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F2015NatSR...5E9996D&amp;rft.au=Bego%C3%B1a+Dobon&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4446898&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACopts" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-154"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-154">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFHollfelderSchlebuschGüntherBabiker2017" class="citation journal cs1">Hollfelder, Nina; Schlebusch, Carina M.; Günther, Torsten; Babiker, Hiba; Hassan, Hisham Y.; Jakobsson, Mattias (2017-08-24). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5587336">"Northeast African genomic variation shaped by the continuity of indigenous groups and Eurasian migrations"</a>. <i>PLOS Genetics</i>. <b>13</b> (8): e1006976. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1371%2Fjournal.pgen.1006976">10.1371/journal.pgen.1006976</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/ISSN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISSN (identifier)">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/issn/1553-7404">1553-7404</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5587336">5587336</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28837655">28837655</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=PLOS+Genetics&amp;rft.atitle=Northeast+African+genomic+variation+shaped+by+the+continuity+of+indigenous+groups+and+Eurasian+migrations&amp;rft.volume=13&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=e1006976&amp;rft.date=2017-08-24&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.n